ZH: 我们每天都要在神龛上供奉点香。
EN: We need to light some incense on the altar every day.

ZH: 在传统的中国文化中，人们会把祖先供奉在家庭神龛里。
EN: In traditional Chinese culture, people would place their ancestors in the family shrine.

ZH: 这个古庙供奉了一尊受人崇拜的神明。
EN: This ancient temple worships a widely revered deity.

ZH: 她每年都会到寺庙去供奉一些水果和花朵。
EN: She goes to the temple every year to offer fruits and flowers.

ZH: 这个寺庙的僧侣天天都会供奉佛祖。
EN: The monks in this temple perform daily rituals to pay homage to the Buddha.

ZH: 这座庙里供奉的神像非常庄严。
EN: The statue worshipped in this temple is very solemn.

ZH: 他把一朵玫瑰供奉给了教堂里的圣母像。
EN: He offered a rose to the statue of the Virgin Mary in the church.

ZH: 她仔细地给每个神像供奉上香。
EN: She carefully lights incense for each deity.

ZH: 在清明节，人们会供奉食品和鲜花到坟墓上。
EN: People offer food and fresh flowers at graves on Tomb-Sweeping Day.

ZH: 在新春佳节，每个家庭都要供奉一台年夜饭。
EN: Every family needs to prepare a grand dinner for the Chinese New Year.

ZH: 这座庙宇供奉了菩萨和观音。
EN: This temple houses statues of Bodhisattvas and Guanyin.

ZH: 祭司将祭品供奉在祭坛上。
EN: The priest offers the sacrifices on the altar.

ZH: 她信仰着一位当地的圣人，每周会去供奉一次。
EN: She believes in a local saint and offers homage once a week.

ZH: 民间信仰中经常会有一些非常特殊的神像供奉。
EN: There are often some very special idols worshipped in folk religions.

ZH: 这个文化中心里供奉了一尊民间传说的英雄雕像。
EN: The cultural center houses a statue of a legendary hero.

ZH: 他将自己的偶像供奉在书桌上。
EN: He displays his idols on the desk.

ZH: 维护寺庙的僧侣需要每天供奉三餐。
EN: The monks who maintain the temple need to be offered three meals a day.

ZH: 这座祠堂供奉了具有地方特色的神灵。
EN: This ancestral hall worships local deities with distinctive characteristics.

ZH: 他为了表示敬意，在资助这所学校的时候，在学校内供奉了一个雕像。
EN: In order to show respect, he funded a statue in the school to pay homage.

ZH: 这位音乐家的肖像供奉在音乐学院大厅里。
EN: The portrait of this musician is displayed in the hall of the music academy.
